$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\displaystyle\lim_{x\to\infty}\dfrac{3x^2}{e^x}
\\\\
&=\displaystyle\lim_{x\to\infty}\dfrac{\dfrac{d}{dx}\left[3x^2\right]}{\dfrac{d}{dx}[e^{x}]}\qquad\gray{\text{l’Hôpital’s rule}}
\\\\
&=\displaystyle\lim_{x\to\infty}\dfrac{6x}{e^x}
\\\\
&=\displaystyle\lim_{x\to\infty}\dfrac{\dfrac{d}{dx}\left[6x\right]}{\dfrac{d}{dx}[e^{x}]}\qquad\gray{\text{l’Hôpital’s rule}}
\\\\
&=\displaystyle\lim_{x\to\infty}\dfrac{6}{e^x}
\\\\
&=0
\end{align}$

Note that we used l’Hôpital’s rule *twice*, because the first time we used it, we ended with the indeterminate form $\dfrac{\infty}{\infty}$ too.

Also note that we were only able to use l’Hôpital’s rule because the limit $\displaystyle\lim_{x\to\infty}\dfrac{\dfrac{d}{dx}\left[6x\right]}{\dfrac{d}{dx}[e^{x}]}$ can actually be determined.

